# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development.
For Vercel deployment, add these variables in the Vercel dashboard.

## Database
# 
# If using Vercel Supabase integration (recommended):
# - POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL and POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING are automatically provided
# - No need to set these manually in Vercel
# - For local development, you can set them manually or use DATABASE_URL/DIRECT_URL
#
# For manual Supabase setup:
# - POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL: Use the connection pooling URL (pooler.supabase.com, port 6543)
#   Format: postgresql://postgres.[project-ref]:[password]@aws-0-[region].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true
# - POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING: Use the direct connection URL (port 5432)
#   Format: postgresql://postgres.[project-ref]:[password]@aws-0-[region].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
#
# For Vercel Postgres or other PostgreSQL (if not using Vercel Supabase integration):
# - Modify prisma/schema.prisma to use DATABASE_URL and DIRECT_URL instead
# - DATABASE_URL: Standard PostgreSQL connection string
# - DIRECT_URL: Same as DATABASE_URL (or omit if not using connection pooling)

# Vercel Supabase integration (automatically provided in Vercel, set manually for local dev)
POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL="postgresql://user:password@host:port/database?schema=public"
POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING="postgresql://user:password@host:port/database?schema=public"

# Alternative: Standard names (if not using Vercel Supabase integration)
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@host:port/database?schema=public"
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://user:password@host:port/database?schema=public"

